The util values are nearly identical on both kernels (~332 vs ~328). The autogroup sysctl defaults to 1, so during exit with PF_EXITING, groups differ and the early bail doesn't trigger. I need to set `sysctl_sched_autogroup_enabled=0` to trigger the bug.

